    <h1>Privacy Policy - Melody Rush (MR)</h1>

    <p class="date">
        Last updated: May 22, 2026
    </p>

    <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Melody Rush (MR)</strong>
        collects, uses, stores, and protects user information.
    </p>

    <p>
        By using the game, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

    <p>
        <strong>Melody Rush (MR)</strong> does not directly collect personally
        identifiable information such as:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Full names</li>
        <li>Addresses</li>
        <li>Phone numbers</li>
        <li>Passwords</li>
        <li>Personal photographs</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        However, the game may process limited technical or gameplay-related
        information through integrated third-party services required for
        gameplay functionality.
    </p>

    <p>
        This information may include:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Device information</li>
        <li>Operating system version</li>
        <li>Crash logs and diagnostics</li>
        <li>Gameplay progress and save data</li>
        <li>Country or region</li>
        <li>Anonymous identifiers required for cloud saving and account persistence</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Third-Party Services</h2>

    <p>
        Melody Rush (MR) may use trusted third-party services to support
        gameplay functionality, cloud saving, and in-app purchases.
    </p>

    <p>
        These services may include:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>PlayFab (cloud save and online functionality)</li>
        <li>Google Play Services</li>
        <li>Unity Gaming Services</li>
        <li>Unity In-App Purchasing (IAP)</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        These providers may process technical information necessary for
        the game to function properly.
    </p>

    <p>
        Each third-party provider is responsible for its own privacy and
        data handling practices.
    </p>

    <h2>3. How Information Is Used</h2>

    <p>
        Information may be used to:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Save player progress</li>
        <li>Provide online functionality</li>
        <li>Restore cloud save data</li>
        <li>Improve stability and performance</li>
        <li>Fix bugs and crashes</li>
        <li>Verify in-app purchases</li>
        <li>Prevent abuse or fraudulent activity</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Account and Data Deletion</h2>

    <p>
        <strong>Melody Rush (MR)</strong> allows users to request or perform
        account deletion.
    </p>

    <div class="highlight-box">
        <h3>Delete your account from inside the game</h3>

        <p>
            Users can permanently delete their account and associated
            gameplay data directly from within the game:
        </p>

        <p>
            <strong>
                Settings → Account → Delete Account
            </strong>
        </p>

        <p>
            When an account is deleted, associated gameplay progress and
            cloud save data linked to the account may also be permanently removed.
        </p>
    </div>

    <h3>Need help?</h3>

    <p>
        If you are unable to access the in-game deletion feature, you may
        contact support to request account or data deletion:
    </p>

    <p>
        <code>thegolmusicgame@gmail.com</code>
    </p>

    <p>
        Please include the subject:
    </p>

    <p>
        <code>Melody Rush Account Deletion Request</code>
    </p>

    <p>
        Requests are typically processed within 7 business days.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Children's Privacy</h2>

    <p>
        Melody Rush (MR) is not intentionally directed toward children
        below the minimum age required under applicable local laws.
    </p>

    <p>
        We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Data Security</h2>

    <p>
        Reasonable measures are taken to protect information handled through
        trusted third-party services. However, no online service can guarantee
        complete security.
    </p>

    <h2>7. External Links</h2>

    <p>
        The game may contain links to external websites or services.
        We are not responsible for the content or privacy practices of
        third-party websites.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>

    <p>
        This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time.
        Any changes will be reflected on this page with an updated revision date.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Contact</h2>

    <p>
        If you have questions regarding this Privacy Policy, your account,
        or your data, contact:
    </p>

    <p>
        <code>thegolmusicgame@gmail.com</code>
    </p>

